<br>
thats a good point..  Remember I never said I do it to get exp.. Thats a side product, (I do like it though) I do it for the competition.  If the exp is shared then how will one know when they get the kill or not?  If I'm in a really good group I will not nuke as hard as I normally do.. typical ssra mob I will nuke twice before its dead in a normal group.. If I'm competing (ksing) then up to 7 or 8 nukes. I just won't nuke 7 or 8 times per kill if I want to share a bit. (couldn't keep up that pace anyway) So I don't always share on purpose.  <br>
<br>
One thing I think is great about raid exp is when I am in a really good group and doing my normal 2 nukes per kill and getting exp every time then people looking AT ME thinking I am overnuking when I am just doing my job but thats a case of a poorly made group so that can be fixed.<br>
<br>
Competition moves along as slow paced raid.. I know its not all fun for all classes at all times but I seriously don't think shared exp will change this and could take fun away from high DPS classes.<br>
<br>
Overnuking aggro is a concern but isn't that part of the fun too? should raids be so perfect?<br>
<br>
<br>
Impudent.. Make a cleric group and rotate people within those groups so they can take a bit of a rest.  or make the cleric group stacked with high DPS so they get their share..<br>
<br>
I don't want anyone on a raid to be bored.  BAD thing.<br>
